com.jme3.scene.plugins.blender.constraints
Enum ConstraintType

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<ConstraintType>
      com.jme3.scene.plugins.blender.constraints.ConstraintType
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ConstraintType>
public enum ConstraintType
extends java.lang.Enum<ConstraintType>

Constraint types. Definitions taken from blender sources, file: DNA_constraint_types.h. Constraint id's the same as used in blender. The constraints might have duplicated type ids, depending on the blender version. The purpose of this enum is to combine class name and the constraint type (id).

getLastDefinedTypeValue

public static int getLastDefinedTypeValue()
This method returns the type value of the last defined constraint. It can be used for allocating tables for storing constraint procedures since not all type values from 0 to the last value are used.

Returns:
the type value of the last defined constraint
